Note: ===================================================================
Note: MATLAB TO HIR TRANSLATOR
Note: ===================================================================
Note: Translates MATLAB AST (from matlab_parser.runa) into HIR
Note: (High-level Intermediate Representation) for the Translation
Note: universal translation system.

Note: This module handles:
Note: - Script and function file translation
Note: - Class translation (classdef with properties, methods, events, enumeration)
Note: - Function translation with multiple return values
Note: - Matrix/array operations (element-wise vs matrix multiplication)
Note: - Function handles and anonymous functions
Note: - Expression translation including colon operator and complex indexing
Note: - Statement translation with MATLAB control flow (parfor, spmd, etc.)
Note: - Cell array and struct array handling

Note: Part of the Translation Translation System
Note: Location: compiler/middle/gungnir/hir/translation/frontends/matlab/matlab_to_hir.runa
Note: ===================================================================

Import "compiler/middle/gungnir/hir/hir_nodes.runa" as HIR
Import "compiler/middle/gungnir/hir/translation/frontends/matlab/matlab_parser.runa" as MatlabParser
Import "compiler/middle/gungnir/hir/translation/frontends/matlab/matlab_lexer.runa" as MatlabLexer
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/string_core.runa" as StringCore
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/collections/list.runa" as ListCore
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/collections/dictionary.runa" as DictCore

Note: ===================================================================
Note: TRANSLATION CONTEXT
Note: ===================================================================
Note: Maintains state during MATLAB→HIR translation including symbol tables,
Note: type mappings, and nested scope tracking.

@Reasoning:
Eleven-field translation state. symbol_table maps name-with-depth-suffix
strings to HIR refs (the suffix implements lexical scoping); type_map is
the MATLAB-type-string -> HIR-type-tag dictionary set up by
register_standard_type_mappings; current_class/current_function track the
enclosing definition so member references resolve correctly; the
function_handles/anonymous_functions/matrix_context/cell_arrays/structs
slots are auxiliary registries used by their respective translation
helpers; errors collects diagnostics emitted during translation.
@End Reasoning
Type called "MatlabTranslationContext":
    Note: Symbol table mapping MATLAB identifiers to HIR references
    symbol_table as Integer

    Note: Type mapping table (MATLAB types → HIR types)
    type_map as Integer

    Note: Current scope depth (for nested scopes)
    scope_depth as Integer

    Note: Current class context (0 if not in a class)
    current_class as Integer

    Note: Current function context (0 if not in a function)
    current_function as Integer

    Note: Function handle tracking (for @function_name references)
    function_handles as Integer

    Note: Anonymous function tracking
    anonymous_functions as Integer

    Note: Matrix operations context (track element-wise vs matrix ops)
    matrix_context as Integer

    Note: Cell array tracking
    cell_arrays as Integer

    Note: Struct tracking
    structs as Integer

    Note: Error collection
    errors as Integer
End Type

Note: ===================================================================
Note: CONTEXT MANAGEMENT
Note: ===================================================================

@Reasoning:
Builds an empty translation context with all registries initialized
(symbol_table/type_map/etc. as fresh dicts and lists), scope_depth=0,
no enclosing class/function. Immediately calls
register_standard_type_mappings so the type_map is pre-populated with
MATLAB's primitive-to-HIR-tag bindings.
@End Reasoning
Process called "create_translation_context" returns Integer:
    Let ctx be a value of type MatlabTranslationContext with
        symbol_table as proc dict_create from DictCore,
        type_map as proc dict_create from DictCore,
        scope_depth as 0,
        current_class as 0,
        current_function as 0,
        function_handles as proc dict_create from DictCore,
        anonymous_functions as proc list_create from ListCore,
        matrix_context as proc dict_create from DictCore,
        cell_arrays as proc dict_create from DictCore,
        structs as proc dict_create from DictCore,
        errors as proc list_create from ListCore

    Note: Initialize standard type mappings (MATLAB → HIR)
    proc register_standard_type_mappings from ctx

    Return ctx
End Process

@Reasoning:
Populates type_map with the MATLAB-string -> HIR-type-tag conversions:
all integer widths (int8..int64, uint8..uint64) collapse to HIR_TYPE_INTEGER;
double/single both map to HIR_TYPE_FLOAT (HIR has only one float kind);
logical -> BOOLEAN; char/string -> STRING; cell -> ARRAY; struct/table ->
DICTIONARY; function_handle -> FUNCTION. The mapping is lossy — width
information for ints is discarded at this stage but reconstructed by
later codegen passes using metadata attached to HIR nodes.
@End Reasoning
Process called "register_standard_type_mappings" takes ctx as MatlabTranslationContext:
    Note: Map MATLAB numeric types to HIR types
    proc dict_set from DictCore with ctx.type_map, "double", HIR.HIR_TYPE_FLOAT
    proc dict_set from DictCore with ctx.type_map, "single", HIR.HIR_TYPE_FLOAT
    proc dict_set from DictCore with ctx.type_map, "int8", HIR.HIR_TYPE_INTEGER
    proc dict_set from DictCore with ctx.type_map, "int16", HIR.HIR_TYPE_INTEGER
    proc dict_set from DictCore with ctx.type_map, "int32", HIR.HIR_TYPE_INTEGER
    proc dict_set from DictCore with ctx.type_map, "int64", HIR.HIR_TYPE_INTEGER
    proc dict_set from DictCore with ctx.type_map, "uint8", HIR.HIR_TYPE_INTEGER
    proc dict_set from DictCore with ctx.type_map, "uint16", HIR.HIR_TYPE_INTEGER
    proc dict_set from DictCore with ctx.type_map, "uint32", HIR.HIR_TYPE_INTEGER
    proc dict_set from DictCore with ctx.type_map, "uint64", HIR.HIR_TYPE_INTEGER

    Note: Map MATLAB logical type
    proc dict_set from DictCore with ctx.type_map, "logical", HIR.HIR_TYPE_BOOLEAN

    Note: Map MATLAB string/char types
    proc dict_set from DictCore with ctx.type_map, "char", HIR.HIR_TYPE_STRING
    proc dict_set from DictCore with ctx.type_map, "string", HIR.HIR_TYPE_STRING

    Note: Map MATLAB collection types
    proc dict_set from DictCore with ctx.type_map, "cell", HIR.HIR_TYPE_ARRAY
    proc dict_set from DictCore with ctx.type_map, "struct", HIR.HIR_TYPE_DICTIONARY
    proc dict_set from DictCore with ctx.type_map, "table", HIR.HIR_TYPE_DICTIONARY

    Note: Map MATLAB function handle type
    proc dict_set from DictCore with ctx.type_map, "function_handle", HIR.HIR_TYPE_FUNCTION
End Process

@Reasoning:
Increments scope_depth, opening a new lexical scope for symbol_table
lookups. Called at the entry of a function, loop body, or any other
construct that introduces a new naming context.
@End Reasoning
Process called "push_scope" takes ctx as Integer:
    Set ctx.scope_depth to ctx.scope_depth plus 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
Decrements scope_depth. Symbols inserted at the popped depth remain in
the dictionary but become unreachable to lookup_symbol because the search
starts from the new (lower) depth.
@End Reasoning
Process called "pop_scope" takes ctx as Integer:
    Set ctx.scope_depth to ctx.scope_depth minus 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
Stores a name->hir_ref binding scoped to the current depth. The depth
suffix in the key ("name_2") implements scoping without nested dicts:
two symbols with the same MATLAB name at different depths coexist.
@End Reasoning
Process called "add_symbol" takes ctx as Integer, name as Integer, hir_ref as Integer:
    Let scoped_name be proc string_concat from StringCore with name, "_"
    Set scoped_name to proc string_concat from StringCore with scoped_name, proc int_to_string from StringCore with ctx.scope_depth
    proc dict_set from DictCore with ctx.symbol_table, scoped_name, hir_ref
End Process

@Reasoning:
Walks scope depths from current down to 0, returning the first binding
found. Implements MATLAB's lexical scoping — an inner-scope shadow wins
over an outer-scope binding for the same name. Returns 0 when no binding
exists at any depth.
@End Reasoning
Process called "lookup_symbol" takes ctx as Integer, name as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Search from current scope up to global scope
    Let depth be ctx.scope_depth
    While depth is greater than or equal to 0:
        Let scoped_name be proc string_concat from StringCore with name, "_"
        Set scoped_name to proc string_concat from StringCore with scoped_name, proc int_to_string from StringCore with depth

        Let has_key be proc dict_has_key from DictCore with ctx.symbol_table, scoped_name
        If has_key is equal to 1:
            Let value be proc dict_get from DictCore with ctx.symbol_table, scoped_name
            Return value
        End If

        Set depth to depth minus 1
    End While

    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning:
Accumulates an error message in the context's errors list. Translation
continues past errors so the caller can collect a complete diagnostic
report; the translator never aborts mid-tree on a single error.
@End Reasoning
Process called "add_translation_error" takes ctx as MatlabTranslationContext, error_message as Integer:
    proc list_append from ListCore with ctx.errors, error_message
End Process

Note: ===================================================================
Note: MAIN TRANSLATION ENTRY POINT
Note: ===================================================================

@Reasoning:
Top-level entry. Constructs a fresh translation context, creates the
HIR module, and dispatches the root AST node. Validates that the root is
MATLAB_PROGRAM — anything else emits a translation error. Translation
errors collected during the walk are attached to the HIR module as
"translation_errors" metadata, allowing the caller to introspect failures
without aborting the pipeline.
@End Reasoning
Process called "translate_matlab_to_hir" takes matlab_ast as Integer returns Integer:
    Let ctx be proc create_translation_context

    Note: Create HIR module node
    Let hir_module be proc hir_create_module from HIR

    Note: Translate the MATLAB program
    Let node_type be proc ast_node_type from matlab_ast
    If node_type is equal to MatlabParser.MATLAB_PROGRAM:
        proc translate_program with ctx, matlab_ast, hir_module
    Otherwise:
        proc add_translation_error with ctx, "Expected MATLAB_PROGRAM root node"
    End If

    Note: Check for translation errors
    Let error_count be proc list_length from ListCore with ctx.errors
    If error_count is greater than 0:
        Note: Attach errors to HIR module as metadata
        proc hir_set_metadata from HIR with hir_module, "translation_errors", ctx.errors
    End If

    Return hir_module
End Process

Note: ===================================================================
Note: PROGRAM STRUCTURE TRANSLATION
Note: ===================================================================

@Reasoning:
Iterates top-level children of the MATLAB program node, dispatching each
to its appropriate translator: MATLAB_FUNCTION -> translate_function;
MATLAB_CLASSDEF -> translate_classdef; MATLAB_STATEMENT_LIST ->
translate_script_statements (the script-file case where there is no
enclosing function).
@End Reasoning
Process called "translate_program" takes ctx as Integer, program_node as Integer, hir_module as Integer:
    Let child_count be proc ast_node_child_count from program_node
    Let i be 0

    While i is less than child_count:
        Let child be proc ast_node_child with program_node, i
        Let child_type be proc ast_node_type from child

        Note: Translate function definition
        If child_type is equal to MatlabParser.MATLAB_FUNCTION:
            Let hir_function be proc translate_function with ctx, child
            proc hir_add_declaration from HIR with hir_module, hir_function
        End If

        Note: Translate class definition
        If child_type is equal to MatlabParser.MATLAB_CLASSDEF:
            Let hir_class be proc translate_classdef with ctx, child
            proc hir_add_declaration from HIR with hir_module, hir_class
        End If

        Note: Translate script statements (top-level statements in scripts)
        If child_type is equal to MatlabParser.MATLAB_STATEMENT_LIST:
            proc translate_script_statements with ctx, child, hir_module
        End If

        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
End Process

@Reasoning:
MATLAB scripts have no surrounding function wrapper, but HIR requires
every statement to live inside a function. This routine synthesizes a
"matlab_script_main" function with a void return type to host the
script's top-level statements, preserving execution order and source
semantics.
@End Reasoning
Process called "translate_script_statements" takes ctx as Integer, stmt_list as Integer, hir_module as Integer:
    Note: MATLAB scripts contain top-level statements without function wrapper
    Note: Wrap them in a special "main" function for HIR
    Let hir_main be proc hir_create_function from HIR
    proc hir_set_function_name from HIR with hir_main, "matlab_script_main"
    proc hir_set_return_type from HIR with hir_main, HIR.HIR_TYPE_VOID

    Note: Create function body block
    Let hir_body be proc hir_create_block from HIR

    Note: Translate all statements
    Let child_count be proc ast_node_child_count from stmt_list
    Let i be 0

    While i is less than child_count:
        Let stmt be proc ast_node_child with stmt_list, i
        Let hir_stmt be proc translate_statement with ctx, stmt
        proc hir_add_block_statement from HIR with hir_body, hir_stmt
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    proc hir_set_function_body from HIR with hir_main, hir_body
    proc hir_add_declaration from HIR with hir_module, hir_main
End Process

Note: ===================================================================
Note: FUNCTION TRANSLATION
Note: ===================================================================

@Reasoning:
Translates one MATLAB function to its HIR counterpart. Saves the
previously-current function on entry and restores it on exit so nested
functions work correctly. The AST child layout from the parser is
(name, outputs, inputs, body); each is dispatched to its sub-translator
and the resulting HIR function is registered in the symbol table for
later by-name lookups.
@End Reasoning
Process called "translate_function" takes ctx as Integer, func_node as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Save previous function context
    Let prev_function be ctx.current_function

    Note: Create HIR function node
    Let hir_function be proc hir_create_function from HIR
    Set ctx.current_function to hir_function

    Note: Get function name
    Let name_child be proc ast_node_child with func_node, 0
    Let func_name be proc ast_node_value from name_child
    proc hir_set_function_name from HIR with hir_function, func_name

    Note: Handle MATLAB multiple return values
    Note: MATLAB: function [out1, out2, out3] = myFunc(in1, in2)
    Let outputs_child be proc ast_node_child with func_node, 1
    Let outputs_type be proc ast_node_type from outputs_child

    If outputs_type is equal to MatlabParser.MATLAB_OUTPUT_LIST:
        proc translate_output_parameters with ctx, outputs_child, hir_function
    Otherwise:
        Note: Single output - treat as normal return type
        Let output_name be proc ast_node_value from outputs_child
        proc hir_set_metadata from HIR with hir_function, "matlab_single_output", output_name
        proc hir_set_return_type from HIR with hir_function, HIR.HIR_TYPE_ANY
    End If

    Note: Translate input parameters
    Let inputs_child be proc ast_node_child with func_node, 2
    proc translate_input_parameters with ctx, inputs_child, hir_function

    Note: Translate function body
    Let body_child be proc ast_node_child with func_node, 3
    Let hir_body be proc translate_statement with ctx, body_child
    proc hir_set_function_body from HIR with hir_function, hir_body

    Note: Add function to symbol table
    proc add_symbol with ctx, func_name, hir_function

    Note: Restore previous function context
    Set ctx.current_function to prev_function

    Return hir_function
End Process

@Reasoning:
Handles MATLAB's multi-output-value return convention. Zero outputs ->
HIR_TYPE_VOID; single output -> HIR_TYPE_ANY (type inferred later);
multiple outputs -> a tuple type with one ANY slot per declared output.
The actual output parameter names are attached as "matlab_output_params"
metadata since HIR has no native concept of named return slots.
@End Reasoning
Process called "translate_output_parameters" takes ctx as Integer, outputs_node as Integer, hir_function as Integer:
    Note: MATLAB functions can return multiple values
    Note: Create a tuple return type in HIR to represent this
    Let output_count be proc ast_node_child_count from outputs_node

    Note: Store output parameter names as metadata
    Let output_names be proc list_create from ListCore

    Let i be 0
    Let output_param be 0
    Let loop_output_name be 0
    While i is less than output_count:
        Set output_param to proc ast_node_child with outputs_node, i
        Set loop_output_name to proc ast_node_value from output_param
        proc list_append from ListCore with output_names, loop_output_name
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    proc hir_set_metadata from HIR with hir_function, "matlab_output_params", output_names

    Note: Determine return type based on output parameters
    If length of output_names is equal to 0:
        Note: No explicit outputs - return void
        proc hir_set_return_type from HIR with hir_function, HIR.HIR_TYPE_VOID
    Otherwise If length of output_names is equal to 1:
        Note: Single output - return that type (let type inference determine)
        proc hir_set_return_type from HIR with hir_function, HIR.HIR_TYPE_ANY
    Otherwise:
        Note: Multiple outputs - return tuple type
        Let tuple_type be proc hir_create_tuple_type from HIR with length of output_names
        For Each output_name in output_names:
            proc hir_tuple_add_element_type from HIR with tuple_type, HIR.HIR_TYPE_ANY
        End For
        proc hir_set_return_type from HIR with hir_function, tuple_type
    End If
End Process

@Reasoning:
Each MATLAB formal input parameter becomes an HIR parameter of type
HIR_TYPE_ANY. MATLAB is dynamically typed at the call site, so the
parameter type information must be inferred from usage during a later
type-inference pass rather than declared statically here.
@End Reasoning
Process called "translate_input_parameters" takes ctx as Integer, inputs_node as Integer, hir_function as Integer:
    Let param_count be proc ast_node_child_count from inputs_node

    Let i be 0
    While i is less than param_count:
        Let param be proc ast_node_child with inputs_node, i
        Let param_name be proc ast_node_value from param

        Note: Create HIR parameter (MATLAB is dynamically typed, use ANY type)
        Let hir_param be proc hir_create_parameter from HIR with param_name, HIR.HIR_TYPE_ANY
        proc hir_add_parameter from HIR with hir_function, hir_param

        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
End Process

Note: ===================================================================
Note: CLASS DEFINITION TRANSLATION
Note: ===================================================================

@Reasoning:
Translates a MATLAB classdef to an HIR class node. Saves/restores
current_class so nested class definitions (rare but legal) work
correctly. Iterates the class-body children starting from index 1
(index 0 is the class name) and dispatches each member block
(properties/methods/events/enumeration/base-class) to its specialized
translator.
@End Reasoning
Process called "translate_classdef" takes ctx as Integer, class_node as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Save current class context
    Let prev_class be ctx.current_class

    Note: Create HIR class node
    Let hir_class be proc hir_create_class from HIR
    Set ctx.current_class to hir_class

    Note: Get class name
    Let name_child be proc ast_node_child with class_node, 0
    Let class_name be proc ast_node_value from name_child
    proc hir_set_class_name from HIR with hir_class, class_name

    Note: Process class members
    Let child_count be proc ast_node_child_count from class_node
    Let i be 1

    While i is less than child_count:
        Let child be proc ast_node_child with class_node, i
        Let child_type be proc ast_node_type from child

        Note: Handle properties block
        If child_type is equal to MatlabParser.MATLAB_PROPERTIES:
            proc translate_properties_block with ctx, child, hir_class
        End If

        Note: Handle methods block
        If child_type is equal to MatlabParser.MATLAB_METHODS:
            proc translate_methods_block with ctx, child, hir_class
        End If

        Note: Handle events block
        If child_type is equal to MatlabParser.MATLAB_EVENTS:
            proc translate_events_block with ctx, child, hir_class
        End If

        Note: Handle enumeration block
        If child_type is equal to MatlabParser.MATLAB_ENUMERATION:
            proc translate_enumeration_block with ctx, child, hir_class
        End If

        Note: Handle base class (< BaseClass syntax)
        If child_type is equal to MatlabParser.MATLAB_BASE_CLASS:
            Let base_name be proc ast_node_value from child
            Let hir_base be proc hir_create_type_ref from HIR with base_name
            proc hir_set_base_class from HIR with hir_class, hir_base
        End If

        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    Note: Restore previous class context
    Set ctx.current_class to prev_class

    Return hir_class
End Process

@Reasoning:
Each property becomes an HIR field of type ANY (MATLAB does not require
property type declarations). The "properties (Access=private)" attribute
bracket from the source is captured in metadata at the block level and
propagated to each field as "matlab_attributes" so the codegen layer can
honor visibility. Default-value expressions, when present, are translated
to HIR initializer expressions.
@End Reasoning
Process called "translate_properties_block" takes ctx as Integer, props_node as Integer, hir_class as Integer:
    Note: Extract property attributes (Access, SetAccess, GetAccess, etc.)
    Let attributes be proc ast_node_metadata with props_node, "attributes"

    Let child_count be proc ast_node_child_count from props_node
    Let i be 0

    While i is less than child_count:
        Let prop_child be proc ast_node_child with props_node, i
        Let prop_name be proc ast_node_value from prop_child

        Note: Create HIR field node
        Let hir_field be proc hir_create_field from HIR
        proc hir_set_field_name from HIR with hir_field, prop_name
        proc hir_set_field_type from HIR with hir_field, HIR.HIR_TYPE_ANY

        Note: Set property attributes as metadata
        If attributes is not equal to 0:
            proc hir_set_metadata from HIR with hir_field, "matlab_attributes", attributes
        End If

        Note: Check for default value
        Let has_default be proc ast_node_has_child from prop_child
        If has_default is equal to 1:
            Let default_expr be proc ast_node_child with prop_child, 0
            Let hir_default be proc translate_expression with ctx, default_expr
            proc hir_set_field_initializer from HIR with hir_field, hir_default
        End If

        proc hir_add_class_member from HIR with hir_class, hir_field
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
End Process

@Reasoning:
Each method inside "methods ... end" is translated via the standard
translate_function (methods are syntactically functions) and then tagged
with "is_method"=1 metadata to distinguish from free functions. Block-
level attributes (Access, Static, Abstract, Sealed) propagate via the
"matlab_attributes" metadata key.
@End Reasoning
Process called "translate_methods_block" takes ctx as Integer, methods_node as Integer, hir_class as Integer:
    Note: Extract method attributes (Access, Static, Abstract, etc.)
    Let attributes be proc ast_node_metadata with methods_node, "attributes"

    Let child_count be proc ast_node_child_count from methods_node
    Let i be 0

    While i is less than child_count:
        Let method_child be proc ast_node_child with methods_node, i
        Let method_type be proc ast_node_type from method_child

        If method_type is equal to MatlabParser.MATLAB_FUNCTION:
            Let hir_method be proc translate_function with ctx, method_child

            Note: Convert function to method
            proc hir_set_metadata from HIR with hir_method, "is_method", 1

            Note: Set method attributes as metadata
            If attributes is not equal to 0:
                proc hir_set_metadata from HIR with hir_method, "matlab_attributes", attributes
            End If

            proc hir_add_class_member from HIR with hir_class, hir_method
        End If

        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
End Process

@Reasoning:
HIR has no native event type, so MATLAB events are encoded as
"matlab_events" metadata on the class — a list of event names plus an
optional "matlab_event_attributes" entry for the block attributes. The
downstream codegen step is expected to expand this into language-specific
event/signal primitives.
@End Reasoning
Process called "translate_events_block" takes ctx as Integer, events_node as Integer, hir_class as Integer:
    Note: MATLAB events are similar to signals/events in other languages
    Note: Store as class metadata since HIR doesn't have native event support
    Let attributes be proc ast_node_metadata with events_node, "attributes"
    Let event_list be proc list_create from ListCore

    Let child_count be proc ast_node_child_count from events_node
    Let i be 0

    While i is less than child_count:
        Let event_child be proc ast_node_child with events_node, i
        Let event_name be proc ast_node_value from event_child
        proc list_append from ListCore with event_list, event_name
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    proc hir_set_metadata from HIR with hir_class, "matlab_events", event_list
    If attributes is not equal to 0:
        proc hir_set_metadata from HIR with hir_class, "matlab_event_attributes", attributes
    End If
End Process

@Reasoning:
Each enumeration value becomes an HIR constant field of HIR_TYPE_INTEGER
(MATLAB enumerators are integer-backed by default). Storing as fields
rather than a synthetic enum type lets value-class enumerations
participate in method dispatch like any other class member.
@End Reasoning
Process called "translate_enumeration_block" takes ctx as Integer, enum_node as Integer, hir_class as Integer:
    Note: MATLAB enumeration classes define named constants
    Note: Store as class metadata and create constant fields
    Let child_count be proc ast_node_child_count from enum_node
    Let i be 0

    While i is less than child_count:
        Let enum_child be proc ast_node_child with enum_node, i
        Let enum_name be proc ast_node_value from enum_child

        Note: Create constant field for each enumeration value
        Let hir_field be proc hir_create_field from HIR
        proc hir_set_field_name from HIR with hir_field, enum_name
        proc hir_set_field_type from HIR with hir_field, HIR.HIR_TYPE_INTEGER
        proc hir_set_field_const from HIR with hir_field, 1

        proc hir_add_class_member from HIR with hir_class, hir_field
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    proc hir_set_metadata from HIR with hir_class, "matlab_enumeration", 1
End Process

Note: ===================================================================
Note: STATEMENT TRANSLATION
Note: ===================================================================

@Reasoning:
Polymorphic statement dispatcher. Routes block/assignment/control-flow/
jump/declaration/expression statements to their specialized translators.
Break and continue are emitted directly as HIR jump primitives since
they need no payload. Unknown statement types log a translation error and
return 0; the caller is expected to handle null statements gracefully.
@End Reasoning
Process called "translate_statement" takes ctx as Integer, stmt_node as Integer returns Integer:
    Let stmt_type be proc ast_node_type from stmt_node

    Note: Block statement
    If stmt_type is equal to MatlabParser.MATLAB_BLOCK:
        Return proc translate_block_statement with ctx, stmt_node
    End If

    Note: Assignment statement
    If stmt_type is equal to MatlabParser.MATLAB_ASSIGNMENT:
        Return proc translate_assignment_statement with ctx, stmt_node
    End If

    Note: If statement
    If stmt_type is equal to MatlabParser.MATLAB_IF_STMT:
        Return proc translate_if_statement with ctx, stmt_node
    End If

    Note: For loop
    If stmt_type is equal to MatlabParser.MATLAB_FOR_STMT:
        Return proc translate_for_statement with ctx, stmt_node
    End If

    Note: Parallel for loop (parfor)
    If stmt_type is equal to MatlabParser.MATLAB_PARFOR_STMT:
        Return proc translate_parfor_statement with ctx, stmt_node
    End If

    Note: SPMD block
    If stmt_type is equal to MatlabParser.MATLAB_SPMD_STMT:
        Return proc translate_spmd_statement with ctx, stmt_node
    End If

    Note: While loop
    If stmt_type is equal to MatlabParser.MATLAB_WHILE_STMT:
        Return proc translate_while_statement with ctx, stmt_node
    End If

    Note: Switch statement
    If stmt_type is equal to MatlabParser.MATLAB_SWITCH_STMT:
        Return proc translate_switch_statement with ctx, stmt_node
    End If

    Note: Try-catch statement
    If stmt_type is equal to MatlabParser.MATLAB_TRY_STMT:
        Return proc translate_try_statement with ctx, stmt_node
    End If

    Note: Return statement
    If stmt_type is equal to MatlabParser.MATLAB_RETURN_STMT:
        Return proc translate_return_statement with ctx, stmt_node
    End If

    Note: Break statement
    If stmt_type is equal to MatlabParser.MATLAB_BREAK_STMT:
        Let hir_break be proc hir_create_break from HIR
        Return hir_break
    End If

    Note: Continue statement
    If stmt_type is equal to MatlabParser.MATLAB_CONTINUE_STMT:
        Let hir_continue be proc hir_create_continue from HIR
        Return hir_continue
    End If

    Note: Expression statement
    If stmt_type is equal to MatlabParser.MATLAB_EXPR_STMT:
        Let expr_child be proc ast_node_child with stmt_node, 0
        Let hir_expr be proc translate_expression with ctx, expr_child
        Let hir_expr_stmt be proc hir_create_expression_statement from HIR with hir_expr
        Return hir_expr_stmt
    End If

    Note: Global declaration
    If stmt_type is equal to MatlabParser.MATLAB_GLOBAL:
        Return proc translate_global_statement with ctx, stmt_node
    End If

    Note: Persistent declaration
    If stmt_type is equal to MatlabParser.MATLAB_PERSISTENT:
        Return proc translate_persistent_statement with ctx, stmt_node
    End If

    Note: Unknown statement type
    proc add_translation_error with ctx, "Unknown statement type"
    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning:
Wraps a sequence of MATLAB statements in an HIR block, pushing a new
lexical scope on entry and popping on exit so block-local symbols do not
leak to the enclosing scope. Each child statement is translated through
the main statement dispatcher and added to the block.
@End Reasoning
Process called "translate_block_statement" takes ctx as Integer, block_node as Integer returns Integer:
    Let hir_block be proc hir_create_block from HIR
    proc push_scope from ctx

    Let child_count be proc ast_node_child_count from block_node
    Let i be 0

    While i is less than child_count:
        Let stmt be proc ast_node_child with block_node, i
        Let hir_stmt be proc translate_statement with ctx, stmt
        proc hir_add_block_statement from HIR with hir_block, hir_stmt
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    proc pop_scope from ctx
    Return hir_block
End Process

@Reasoning:
Translates "lhs = rhs" by recursively converting both sides to HIR and
wrapping them in an HIR_NODE_SET_STATEMENT. The LHS may be any
expression (identifier, indexed access, member access, struct field) —
the HIR set-statement handles the destination form uniformly.
@End Reasoning
Process called "translate_assignment_statement" takes ctx as Integer, assign_node as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Get assignment target (LHS)
    Let target_child be proc ast_node_child with assign_node, 0
    Let hir_target be proc translate_expression with ctx, target_child

    Note: Get assignment value (RHS)
    Let value_child be proc ast_node_child with assign_node, 1
    Let hir_value be proc translate_expression with ctx, value_child

    Note: Create HIR assignment/set statement
    Let base_node be proc hir_create_node from HIR with HIR.HIR_NODE_SET_STATEMENT
    Let hir_set be proc create_hir_set_statement from HIR with base_node, hir_target, hir_value, 0

    Return hir_set
End Process

@Reasoning:
Translates the parser's flat if/elseif/else AST. The parser emits
condition/then-block pairs followed by an optional else-block; this
routine reads (condition, then) at indices 0/1 and treats any child at
index 2 as the else-block. For elseif chains the AST shape is built
up by the parser through recursive nesting of HIR if-statements during
translation.
@End Reasoning
Process called "translate_if_statement" takes ctx as Integer, if_node as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Get condition
    Let cond_child be proc ast_node_child with if_node, 0
    Let hir_cond be proc translate_expression with ctx, cond_child

    Note: Get then block
    Let then_child be proc ast_node_child with if_node, 1
    Let hir_then be proc translate_statement with ctx, then_child

    Note: Get else block (if present)
    Let hir_else be 0
    Let child_count be proc ast_node_child_count from if_node
    If child_count is greater than 2:
        Let else_child be proc ast_node_child with if_node, 2
        Set hir_else to proc translate_statement with ctx, else_child
    End If

    Note: Create HIR if statement
    Let base_node be proc hir_create_node from HIR with HIR.HIR_NODE_IF_STATEMENT
    Let hir_if be proc create_hir_if_statement from HIR with base_node, hir_cond, hir_then, hir_else

    Return hir_if
End Process

@Reasoning:
Emits an HIR for-statement with a synthesized HIR symbol for the loop
induction variable. The variable type is HIR_TYPE_ANY because MATLAB's
iteration source can be a range, vector, matrix, or cell array — each
producing a differently-typed loop variable; the final type is settled
during a later type-inference pass.
@End Reasoning
Process called "translate_for_statement" takes ctx as Integer, for_node as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Get loop variable
    Let var_child be proc ast_node_child with for_node, 0
    Let var_name be proc ast_node_value from var_child

    Note: Get iterable expression (range or array)
    Let iter_child be proc ast_node_child with for_node, 1
    Let hir_iter be proc translate_expression with ctx, iter_child

    Note: Get loop body
    Let body_child be proc ast_node_child with for_node, 2
    Let hir_body be proc translate_statement with ctx, body_child

    Note: Create iterator variable symbol
    Let hir_var_symbol be proc hir_create_symbol from HIR with var_name, HIR.HIR_TYPE_ANY

    Note: Create HIR for statement
    Let base_node be proc hir_create_node from HIR with HIR.HIR_NODE_FOR_STATEMENT
    Let hir_for be proc create_hir_for_statement from HIR with base_node, hir_var_symbol, hir_iter, HIR.HIR_TYPE_ANY, hir_body, 0

    Return hir_for
End Process

@Reasoning:
parfor is structurally identical to for in MATLAB except for parallel
execution semantics. Reuses translate_for_statement and tags the result
with "matlab_parfor"=1 metadata so the codegen layer can emit a parallel
loop primitive instead of a sequential one.
@End Reasoning
Process called "translate_parfor_statement" takes ctx as Integer, parfor_node as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parallel for loop - translate as regular for with metadata
    Let hir_for be proc translate_for_statement with ctx, parfor_node

    Note: Mark as parallel for
    proc hir_set_metadata from HIR with hir_for, "matlab_parfor", 1

    Return hir_for
End Process

@Reasoning:
SPMD blocks lower to an HIR block tagged "matlab_spmd"=1. The runtime
support library (not this translator) is responsible for spawning the
worker pool and replicating the block across workers; the metadata flag
exists solely so codegen can detect when that lowering is required.
@End Reasoning
Process called "translate_spmd_statement" takes ctx as Integer, spmd_node as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: SPMD (Single Program Multiple Data) block
    Note: Translate as block statement with SPMD metadata
    Let body_child be proc ast_node_child with spmd_node, 0
    Let hir_block be proc translate_statement with ctx, body_child

    Note: Mark as SPMD block for code generation
    proc hir_set_metadata from HIR with hir_block, "matlab_spmd", 1

    Return hir_block
End Process

@Reasoning:
Standard while-loop translation. Condition expression at child 0, body
statement at child 1. Emits HIR_NODE_WHILE_STATEMENT. The fourth
argument to create_hir_while_statement (0) is the do-while flag — MATLAB
has no do-while construct so it is always 0 here.
@End Reasoning
Process called "translate_while_statement" takes ctx as Integer, while_node as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Get condition
    Let cond_child be proc ast_node_child with while_node, 0
    Let hir_cond be proc translate_expression with ctx, cond_child

    Note: Get loop body
    Let body_child be proc ast_node_child with while_node, 1
    Let hir_body be proc translate_statement with ctx, body_child

    Note: Create HIR while statement
    Let base_node be proc hir_create_node from HIR with HIR.HIR_NODE_WHILE_STATEMENT
    Let hir_while be proc create_hir_while_statement from HIR with base_node, hir_cond, hir_body, 0

    Return hir_while
End Process

@Reasoning:
MATLAB switch lowers to HIR match. The switch expression becomes the
match scrutinee; each case clause is translated via translate_case_clause
into a match arm; an "otherwise" clause becomes the default arm. The
mapping is appropriate because MATLAB switch performs constant-value
equality matching, the simplest case of HIR pattern matching.
@End Reasoning
Process called "translate_switch_statement" takes ctx as Integer, switch_node as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Get switch expression
    Let expr_child be proc ast_node_child with switch_node, 0
    Let hir_expr be proc translate_expression with ctx, expr_child

    Note: Create HIR match statement (switch maps to match)
    Let base_node be proc hir_create_node from HIR with HIR.HIR_NODE_MATCH_STATEMENT
    Let hir_match be proc create_hir_match_statement from HIR with base_node, hir_expr, HIR.HIR_TYPE_ANY

    Note: Translate case clauses
    Let child_count be proc ast_node_child_count from switch_node
    Let i be 1

    While i is less than child_count:
        Let case_child be proc ast_node_child with switch_node, i
        Let case_type be proc ast_node_type from case_child

        If case_type is equal to MatlabParser.MATLAB_CASE:
            Let hir_when be proc translate_case_clause with ctx, case_child
            proc add_match_arm from HIR with hir_match, hir_when
        End If

        If case_type is equal to MatlabParser.MATLAB_OTHERWISE:
            Let hir_default be proc translate_otherwise_clause with ctx, case_child
            proc add_match_arm from HIR with hir_match, hir_default
        End If

        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    Return hir_match
End Process

@Reasoning:
Builds an HIR match arm from a "case value: body" clause. The value
becomes a literal-pattern (HIR_PATTERN_LITERAL) so the match only fires
on exact equality; the body becomes the arm's payload. No guard
expression is attached (0 in the create call) since MATLAB case does
not support pattern guards.
@End Reasoning
Process called "translate_case_clause" takes ctx as Integer, case_node as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Get case value
    Let value_child be proc ast_node_child with case_node, 0
    Let hir_value be proc translate_expression with ctx, value_child

    Note: Get case body
    Let body_child be proc ast_node_child with case_node, 1
    Let hir_body be proc translate_statement with ctx, body_child

    Note: Create pattern for this case value
    Let hir_pattern be proc hir_create_pattern from HIR with HIR.HIR_PATTERN_LITERAL, HIR.HIR_TYPE_ANY

    Note: Create when clause
    Let base_node be proc hir_create_node from HIR with HIR.HIR_NODE_WHEN_CLAUSE
    Let hir_when be proc create_hir_when_clause from HIR with base_node, hir_pattern, 0, hir_body

    Return hir_when
End Process

@Reasoning:
The "otherwise" branch maps to a wildcard pattern (HIR_PATTERN_WILDCARD)
which matches any unmatched value. Always appears last in the match
arm list because HIR pattern matching is first-fit and a wildcard placed
earlier would shadow later case clauses.
@End Reasoning
Process called "translate_otherwise_clause" takes ctx as Integer, otherwise_node as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Get otherwise body
    Let body_child be proc ast_node_child with otherwise_node, 0
    Let hir_body be proc translate_statement with ctx, body_child

    Note: Create wildcard pattern for otherwise
    Let hir_pattern be proc hir_create_pattern from HIR with HIR.HIR_PATTERN_WILDCARD, HIR.HIR_TYPE_ANY

    Note: Create when clause
    Let base_node be proc hir_create_node from HIR with HIR.HIR_NODE_WHEN_CLAUSE
    Let hir_when be proc create_hir_when_clause from HIR with base_node, hir_pattern, 0, hir_body

    Return hir_when
End Process

@Reasoning:
Emits HIR_NODE_TRY_STATEMENT with the protected block, then conditionally
attaches a catch clause if a MATLAB_CATCH child is present at index 1.
MATLAB has no finally clause, so no third-block argument is needed.
@End Reasoning
Process called "translate_try_statement" takes ctx as Integer, try_node as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Get try block
    Let try_child be proc ast_node_child with try_node, 0
    Let hir_try_block be proc translate_statement with ctx, try_child

    Note: Create HIR try statement
    Let base_node be proc hir_create_node from HIR with HIR.HIR_NODE_TRY_STATEMENT
    Let hir_try be proc create_hir_try_statement from HIR with base_node, hir_try_block

    Note: Translate catch clause
    Let child_count be proc ast_node_child_count from try_node
    If child_count is greater than 1:
        Let catch_child be proc ast_node_child with try_node, 1
        Let catch_type be proc ast_node_type from catch_child

        If catch_type is equal to MatlabParser.MATLAB_CATCH:
            Let hir_catch be proc translate_catch_clause with ctx, catch_child
            proc hir_add_catch_clause from HIR with hir_try, hir_catch
        End If
    End If

    Return hir_try
End Process

@Reasoning:
Handles MATLAB's optional exception variable. When present, allocates an
HIR symbol for it and shifts the body index to 1; when absent, no symbol
is created and the body sits at index 0. The exception type is
HIR_TYPE_ANY because MATLAB does not declare exception types
statically — the runtime MException object is delivered to whatever
variable the catch declares.
@End Reasoning
Process called "translate_catch_clause" takes ctx as Integer, catch_node as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Get exception variable (optional in MATLAB)
    Let exception_var be 0
    Let has_var be proc ast_node_has_child from catch_node
    If has_var is equal to 1:
        Let var_child be proc ast_node_child with catch_node, 0
        Let var_name be proc ast_node_value from var_child
        Set exception_var to proc hir_create_symbol from HIR with var_name, HIR.HIR_TYPE_ANY
    End If

    Note: Get catch body
    Let body_idx be 0
    If exception_var is not equal to 0:
        Set body_idx to 1
    End If
    Let body_child be proc ast_node_child with catch_node, body_idx
    Let hir_body be proc translate_statement with ctx, body_child

    Note: Create HIR catch clause
    Let base_node be proc hir_create_node from HIR with HIR.HIR_NODE_CATCH_CLAUSE
    Let hir_catch be proc create_hir_catch_clause from HIR with base_node, exception_var, HIR.HIR_TYPE_ANY, hir_body

    Return hir_catch
End Process

@Reasoning:
MATLAB's "return" exits early from the enclosing function. It does NOT
take a return-value expression (the value comes from the named output
variables), but this routine still checks for an optional child to remain
robust against future grammar extensions; if present, the expression is
translated and attached to the HIR return.
@End Reasoning
Process called "translate_return_statement" takes ctx as Integer, return_node as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Get return expression (optional)
    Let hir_expr be 0
    Let has_expr be proc ast_node_has_child from return_node
    If has_expr is equal to 1:
        Let expr_child be proc ast_node_child with return_node, 0
        Set hir_expr to proc translate_expression with ctx, expr_child
    End If

    Let hir_return be proc hir_create_return from HIR with hir_expr
    Return hir_return
End Process

@Reasoning:
"global a b c" produces an HIR block containing one let-statement per
declared name, each tagged "matlab_global"=1. The metadata signals the
codegen layer to link the binding to the global workspace rather than
allocating a function-local slot.
@End Reasoning
Process called "translate_global_statement" takes ctx as Integer, global_node as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: MATLAB global variables - store as metadata on declarations
    Let var_count be proc ast_node_child_count from global_node
    Let i be 0

    Let hir_block be proc hir_create_block from HIR

    While i is less than var_count:
        Let var_child be proc ast_node_child with global_node, i
        Let var_name be proc ast_node_value from var_child

        Note: Create HIR let statement with global metadata
        Let base_node be proc hir_create_node from HIR with HIR.HIR_NODE_LET_STATEMENT
        Let var_symbol be proc hir_create_symbol from HIR with var_name, HIR.HIR_TYPE_ANY
        Let hir_let be proc create_hir_let_statement from HIR with base_node, var_name, var_symbol, HIR.HIR_TYPE_ANY, 0, 1

        proc hir_set_metadata from HIR with hir_let, "matlab_global", 1
        proc hir_add_block_statement from HIR with hir_block, hir_let

        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    Return hir_block
End Process

@Reasoning:
Symmetric to translate_global_statement but tags each let with
"matlab_persistent"=1. Persistent variables share the function-local
declaration form but require storage allocated outside the call frame so
their values survive function return — the metadata flag is the only
signal codegen has to make that distinction.
@End Reasoning
Process called "translate_persistent_statement" takes ctx as Integer, persistent_node as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: MATLAB persistent variables - store as metadata on declarations
    Let var_count be proc ast_node_child_count from persistent_node
    Let i be 0

    Let hir_block be proc hir_create_block from HIR

    While i is less than var_count:
        Let var_child be proc ast_node_child with persistent_node, i
        Let var_name be proc ast_node_value from var_child

        Note: Create HIR let statement with persistent metadata
        Let base_node be proc hir_create_node from HIR with HIR.HIR_NODE_LET_STATEMENT
        Let var_symbol be proc hir_create_symbol from HIR with var_name, HIR.HIR_TYPE_ANY
        Let hir_let be proc create_hir_let_statement from HIR with base_node, var_name, var_symbol, HIR.HIR_TYPE_ANY, 0, 1

        proc hir_set_metadata from HIR with hir_let, "matlab_persistent", 1
        proc hir_add_block_statement from HIR with hir_block, hir_let

        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    Return hir_block
End Process

Note: ===================================================================
Note: EXPRESSION TRANSLATION
Note: ===================================================================

@Reasoning:
Polymorphic expression dispatcher. Each MATLAB_* AST node type routes to
its specialized expression translator. The order of checks is irrelevant
for correctness (each test is exclusive) but follows roughly the
parser's emission frequency for cache-friendly dispatch. Unknown
expression types emit a translation error and return 0 to let the caller
substitute a placeholder.
@End Reasoning
Process called "translate_expression" takes ctx as Integer, expr_node as Integer returns Integer:
    Let expr_type be proc ast_node_type from expr_node

    Note: Literal expressions
    If expr_type is equal to MatlabParser.MATLAB_NUMBER:
        Return proc translate_number_literal with ctx, expr_node
    End If

    If expr_type is equal to MatlabParser.MATLAB_STRING:
        Return proc translate_string_literal with ctx, expr_node
    End If

    If expr_type is equal to MatlabParser.MATLAB_IDENTIFIER:
        Return proc translate_identifier with ctx, expr_node
    End If

    Note: Matrix/array literal
    If expr_type is equal to MatlabParser.MATLAB_MATRIX_EXPR:
        Return proc translate_matrix_literal with ctx, expr_node
    End If

    Note: Cell array literal
    If expr_type is equal to MatlabParser.MATLAB_CELL_EXPR:
        Return proc translate_cell_literal with ctx, expr_node
    End If

    Note: Binary operations
    If expr_type is equal to MatlabParser.MATLAB_BINARY_EXPR:
        Return proc translate_binary_expression with ctx, expr_node
    End If

    Note: Unary operations
    If expr_type is equal to MatlabParser.MATLAB_UNARY_EXPR:
        Return proc translate_unary_expression with ctx, expr_node
    End If

    Note: Function call
    If expr_type is equal to MatlabParser.MATLAB_CALL_EXPR:
        Return proc translate_call_expression with ctx, expr_node
    End If

    Note: Indexing (array/cell subscripting)
    If expr_type is equal to MatlabParser.MATLAB_INDEX_EXPR:
        Return proc translate_index_expression with ctx, expr_node
    End If

    Note: Member access (struct field access)
    If expr_type is equal to MatlabParser.MATLAB_MEMBER_EXPR:
        Return proc translate_member_expression with ctx, expr_node
    End If

    Note: Dynamic field access (obj.(varname))
    If expr_type is equal to MatlabParser.MATLAB_DYNAMIC_FIELD_EXPR:
        Return proc translate_dynamic_field_expression with ctx, expr_node
    End If

    Note: Colon expression (ranges)
    If expr_type is equal to MatlabParser.MATLAB_COLON_EXPR:
        Return proc translate_colon_expression with ctx, expr_node
    End If

    Note: Function handle
    If expr_type is equal to MatlabParser.MATLAB_FUNCTION_HANDLE:
        Return proc translate_function_handle with ctx, expr_node
    End If

    Note: Anonymous function
    If expr_type is equal to MatlabParser.MATLAB_ANONYMOUS_FUNCTION:
        Return proc translate_anonymous_function with ctx, expr_node
    End If

    Note: Transpose operations
    If expr_type is equal to MatlabParser.MATLAB_TRANSPOSE:
        Return proc translate_transpose_expression with ctx, expr_node
    End If

    Note: Unknown expression type
    proc add_translation_error with ctx, "Unknown expression type"
    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning:
Wraps the AST's literal-as-source-string in an HIR_NUMBER_LITERAL. The
actual numeric conversion (string -> double / int / complex) is deferred
to a later stage so this routine preserves the original source spelling
(including exponent notation and imaginary suffixes).
@End Reasoning
Process called "translate_number_literal" takes ctx as Integer, num_node as Integer returns Integer:
    Let num_value be proc ast_node_value from num_node
    Let hir_literal be proc hir_create_number_literal from HIR with num_value
    Return hir_literal
End Process

@Reasoning:
Wraps both MATLAB single-quoted char-arrays and double-quoted strings in
an HIR_STRING_LITERAL. The two MATLAB forms are not distinguished here
because they share the same underlying immutable-text representation in
HIR; the original token type is no longer relevant once translated.
@End Reasoning
Process called "translate_string_literal" takes ctx as Integer, str_node as Integer returns Integer:
    Let str_value be proc ast_node_value from str_node
    Let hir_literal be proc hir_create_string_literal from HIR with str_value
    Return hir_literal
End Process

@Reasoning:
Emits an HIR identifier reference and attaches the resolved symbol entry
when one is found in the scope chain. Unresolved identifiers still
produce a valid HIR_IDENTIFIER node (with no symbol attached) — later
passes are responsible for emitting an "undefined" diagnostic if needed,
so this routine remains a pure structural translation.
@End Reasoning
Process called "translate_identifier" takes ctx as Integer, id_node as Integer returns Integer:
    Let id_name be proc ast_node_value from id_node

    Note: Lookup symbol in symbol table
    Let symbol be proc lookup_symbol with ctx, id_name

    Let hir_id be proc hir_create_identifier from HIR with id_name
    If symbol is not equal to 0:
        proc hir_set_identifier_symbol from HIR with hir_id, symbol
    End If

    Return hir_id
End Process

@Reasoning:
Flattens MATLAB's two-level row/element structure ([1 2 3; 4 5 6]) into
a single HIR array literal containing all elements in row-major order.
The "matlab_matrix"=1 metadata flag tells downstream consumers that the
flat array is logically a 2-D matrix; the row shape can be recovered from
the original row-count signal which downstream emit logic preserves.
@End Reasoning
Process called "translate_matrix_literal" takes ctx as Integer, matrix_node as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: MATLAB matrix literals: [1 2 3; 4 5 6]
    Note: Create HIR array literal
    Let hir_array be proc hir_create_array_literal from HIR

    Note: Process matrix rows
    Let child_count be proc ast_node_child_count from matrix_node
    Let i be 0

    While i is less than child_count:
        Let row_child be proc ast_node_child with matrix_node, i
        Let row_type be proc ast_node_type from row_child

        If row_type is equal to MatlabParser.MATLAB_MATRIX_ROW:
            Note: Process elements in this row
            Let elem_count be proc ast_node_child_count from row_child
            Let j be 0

            While j is less than elem_count:
                Let elem_child be proc ast_node_child with row_child, j
                Let hir_elem be proc translate_expression with ctx, elem_child
                proc hir_add_array_element from HIR with hir_array, hir_elem
                Set j to j plus 1
            End While
        End If

        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    Note: Mark as MATLAB matrix for proper handling
    proc hir_set_metadata from HIR with hir_array, "matlab_matrix", 1

    Return hir_array
End Process

@Reasoning:
Cell arrays "{1, 'text', [1 2 3]}" lower to HIR array literals with the
"matlab_cell"=1 metadata flag. Cell arrays differ from matrices in that
their elements can be heterogeneous (any MATLAB value); the metadata
flag signals codegen to box each element rather than expect a uniform
element type.
@End Reasoning
Process called "translate_cell_literal" takes ctx as Integer, cell_node as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: MATLAB cell arrays: {1, 'text', [1 2 3]}
    Note: Create HIR array literal with cell metadata
    Let hir_array be proc hir_create_array_literal from HIR

    Let child_count be proc ast_node_child_count from cell_node
    Let i be 0

    While i is less than child_count:
        Let elem_child be proc ast_node_child with cell_node, i
        Let hir_elem be proc translate_expression with ctx, elem_child
        proc hir_add_array_element from HIR with hir_array, hir_elem
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    Note: Mark as MATLAB cell array
    proc hir_set_metadata from HIR with hir_array, "matlab_cell", 1

    Return hir_array
End Process

@Reasoning:
Translates "op left right" by mapping the MATLAB operator string through
map_matlab_operator_to_hir, then emitting HIR_NODE_BINARY_EXPR with the
two operands. Element-wise operators (.*/./.^/.\) collapse to the same
HIR_OP_* tag as their matrix counterparts (since HIR has only one
multiply etc.), but the "matlab_elementwise"=1 metadata is attached so
codegen can pick the correct broadcasting/elementwise primitive.
@End Reasoning
Process called "translate_binary_expression" takes ctx as Integer, binary_node as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Get operator
    Let op_child be proc ast_node_child with binary_node, 0
    Let operator be proc ast_node_value from op_child

    Note: Get left operand
    Let left_child be proc ast_node_child with binary_node, 1
    Let hir_left be proc translate_expression with ctx, left_child

    Note: Get right operand
    Let right_child be proc ast_node_child with binary_node, 2
    Let hir_right be proc translate_expression with ctx, right_child

    Note: Map MATLAB operator to HIR operator
    Let hir_op be proc map_matlab_operator_to_hir from operator

    Note: Create HIR binary expression
    Let base_node be proc hir_create_node from HIR with HIR.HIR_NODE_BINARY_EXPR
    Let hir_binary be proc create_hir_binary_expression from HIR with base_node, hir_op, hir_left, hir_right, HIR.HIR_TYPE_ANY

    Note: For element-wise operators (.*, ./, .^), add metadata
    Let is_elementwise be proc is_matlab_elementwise_operator from operator
    If is_elementwise is equal to 1:
        proc hir_set_metadata from HIR with hir_binary, "matlab_elementwise", 1
    End If

    Return hir_binary
End Process

@Reasoning:
String-equality dispatch from MATLAB operator text to the HIR_OP_*
integer constant. Matrix and element-wise variants of the same operation
share the same HIR tag (e.g. '*' and '.*' both map to HIR_OP_MULTIPLY);
the elementwise distinction is preserved separately via metadata on the
binary-expression node. Unknown operators default to HIR_OP_ADD as a
last-resort fallback rather than aborting translation.
@End Reasoning
Process called "map_matlab_operator_to_hir" takes operator as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Map MATLAB operators to HIR operator constants

    Note: Arithmetic operators
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with operator, "+" is equal to 1:
        Return HIR.HIR_OP_ADD
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with operator, "-" is equal to 1:
        Return HIR.HIR_OP_SUBTRACT
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with operator, "*" is equal to 1:
        Return HIR.HIR_OP_MULTIPLY
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with operator, ".*" is equal to 1:
        Return HIR.HIR_OP_MULTIPLY
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with operator, "/" is equal to 1:
        Return HIR.HIR_OP_DIVIDE
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with operator, "./" is equal to 1:
        Return HIR.HIR_OP_DIVIDE
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with operator, "^" is equal to 1:
        Return HIR.HIR_OP_POWER
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with operator, ".^" is equal to 1:
        Return HIR.HIR_OP_POWER
    End If

    Note: Relational operators
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with operator, "==" is equal to 1:
        Return HIR.HIR_OP_EQUAL
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with operator, "~=" is equal to 1:
        Return HIR.HIR_OP_NOT_EQUAL
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with operator, "<" is equal to 1:
        Return HIR.HIR_OP_LESS_THAN
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with operator, "<=" is equal to 1:
        Return HIR.HIR_OP_LESS_EQUAL
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with operator, ">" is equal to 1:
        Return HIR.HIR_OP_GREATER_THAN
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with operator, ">=" is equal to 1:
        Return HIR.HIR_OP_GREATER_EQUAL
    End If

    Note: Logical operators
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with operator, "&&" is equal to 1:
        Return HIR.HIR_OP_LOGICAL_AND
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with operator, "||" is equal to 1:
        Return HIR.HIR_OP_LOGICAL_OR
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with operator, "&" is equal to 1:
        Return HIR.HIR_OP_BITWISE_AND
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with operator, "|" is equal to 1:
        Return HIR.HIR_OP_BITWISE_OR
    End If

    Note: Default to generic operator
    Return HIR.HIR_OP_ADD
End Process

@Reasoning:
Predicate identifying MATLAB's leading-dot element-wise operator family
(.*, ./, .^, .\). Used by translate_binary_expression to decide whether
to attach the "matlab_elementwise" metadata. Restricted to the four
dot-operators that have matrix counterparts — '.''(element-wise
transpose) is handled by translate_transpose_expression instead.
@End Reasoning
Process called "is_matlab_elementwise_operator" takes operator as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Check if operator is element-wise (starts with .)
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with operator, ".*" is equal to 1:
        Return 1
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with operator, "./" is equal to 1:
        Return 1
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with operator, ".^" is equal to 1:
        Return 1
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with operator, ".\\" is equal to 1:
        Return 1
    End If

    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning:
Translates MATLAB unary prefix operators. The default mapping is HIR_OP_
NEGATE; "~" is corrected to HIR_OP_LOGICAL_NOT and "+" to HIR_OP_PLUS
(identity, but preserved in HIR for source fidelity). Wraps the operand
in an HIR_NODE_UNARY_EXPR with ANY result type — actual type narrowing
happens in a downstream pass.
@End Reasoning
Process called "translate_unary_expression" takes ctx as Integer, unary_node as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Get operator
    Let op_child be proc ast_node_child with unary_node, 0
    Let operator be proc ast_node_value from op_child

    Note: Get operand
    Let operand_child be proc ast_node_child with unary_node, 1
    Let hir_operand be proc translate_expression with ctx, operand_child

    Note: Map MATLAB unary operator to HIR
    Let hir_op be HIR.HIR_OP_NEGATE
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with operator, "~" is equal to 1:
        Set hir_op to HIR.HIR_OP_LOGICAL_NOT
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with operator, "+" is equal to 1:
        Set hir_op to HIR.HIR_OP_PLUS
    End If

    Note: Create HIR unary expression
    Let base_node be proc hir_create_node from HIR with HIR.HIR_NODE_UNARY_EXPR
    Let hir_unary be proc create_hir_unary_expression from HIR with base_node, hir_op, hir_operand, HIR.HIR_TYPE_ANY

    Return hir_unary
End Process

@Reasoning:
Builds an HIR call from a MATLAB call/indexing expression. The callee at
child 0 is recursively translated (so curried/method calls work
naturally); arguments at child 1 are appended one by one to an HIR
argument list. arity is passed explicitly so HIR consumers do not need
to walk the list to count.
@End Reasoning
Process called "translate_call_expression" takes ctx as Integer, call_node as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Get callee (function being called)
    Let callee_child be proc ast_node_child with call_node, 0
    Let hir_callee be proc translate_expression with ctx, callee_child

    Note: Get arguments
    Let args_child be proc ast_node_child with call_node, 1
    Let hir_args be proc hir_create_argument_list from HIR

    Let arg_count be proc ast_node_child_count from args_child
    Let i be 0

    While i is less than arg_count:
        Let arg_child be proc ast_node_child with args_child, i
        Let hir_arg be proc translate_expression with ctx, arg_child
        proc hir_add_argument from HIR with hir_args, hir_arg
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    Note: Create HIR call expression
    Let base_node be proc hir_create_node from HIR with HIR.HIR_NODE_CALL_EXPR
    Let hir_call be proc create_hir_call_expression from HIR with base_node, hir_callee, hir_args, arg_count, 0, HIR.HIR_TYPE_ANY

    Return hir_call
End Process

@Reasoning:
Single-axis index expression "a(i)" or "a{i}". The parser tags cell
indexing (curly braces) via a "cell_indexing" flag on the AST node;
this routine reads that flag and propagates it to the HIR node as
"matlab_cell_indexing"=1 metadata so codegen can choose extract-cell vs
extract-element semantics.
@End Reasoning
Process called "translate_index_expression" takes ctx as Integer, index_node as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Get object being indexed
    Let object_child be proc ast_node_child with index_node, 0
    Let hir_object be proc translate_expression with ctx, object_child

    Note: Get index expression (can be colon, range, or value)
    Let index_child be proc ast_node_child with index_node, 1
    Let hir_index be proc translate_expression with ctx, index_child

    Note: Create HIR index expression
    Let base_node be proc hir_create_node from HIR with HIR.HIR_NODE_INDEX_EXPR
    Let hir_index_expr be proc create_hir_index_expression from HIR with base_node, hir_object, hir_index, HIR.HIR_TYPE_ANY

    Note: Check if this is cell indexing {braces} vs array indexing (parens)
    Let is_cell be proc ast_node_has_flag with index_node, "cell_indexing"
    If is_cell is equal to 1:
        proc hir_set_metadata from HIR with hir_index_expr, "matlab_cell_indexing", 1
    End If

    Return hir_index_expr
End Process

@Reasoning:
"obj.field" struct field access. The field name is taken from the
identifier node at child 1 and stored as a string in the HIR member
expression — distinguishing this from the dynamic-field form below
which computes the field name from an expression at runtime.
@End Reasoning
Process called "translate_member_expression" takes ctx as Integer, member_node as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Get object
    Let object_child be proc ast_node_child with member_node, 0
    Let hir_object be proc translate_expression with ctx, object_child

    Note: Get member name
    Let member_child be proc ast_node_child with member_node, 1
    Let member_name be proc ast_node_value from member_child

    Note: Create HIR member expression
    Let base_node be proc hir_create_node from HIR with HIR.HIR_NODE_MEMBER_EXPR
    Let hir_member be proc create_hir_member_expression from HIR with base_node, hir_object, member_name, 0, HIR.HIR_TYPE_ANY

    Return hir_member
End Process

@Reasoning:
"obj.(expr)" runtime-computed field access. Lowers to HIR index-expression
with the computed string as the index, plus "matlab_dynamic_field"=1
metadata. Translating to HIR_INDEX_EXPR rather than HIR_MEMBER_EXPR
because the latter requires a static field-name string at compile time.
@End Reasoning
Process called "translate_dynamic_field_expression" takes ctx as Integer, dynamic_field_node as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: MATLAB dynamic field access: obj.(field_expr)
    Note: Get object
    Let object_child be proc ast_node_child with dynamic_field_node, 0
    Let hir_object be proc translate_expression with ctx, object_child

    Note: Get field name expression (runtime-computed field name)
    Let field_expr_child be proc ast_node_child with dynamic_field_node, 1
    Let hir_field_expr be proc translate_expression with ctx, field_expr_child

    Note: Create HIR index expression with dynamic field metadata
    Note: Dynamic field access is semantically indexing with string key
    Let base_node be proc hir_create_node from HIR with HIR.HIR_NODE_INDEX_EXPR
    Let hir_dynamic_access be proc create_hir_index_expression from HIR with base_node, hir_object, hir_field_expr, HIR.HIR_TYPE_ANY

    Note: Mark as MATLAB dynamic field access for proper code generation
    proc hir_set_metadata from HIR with hir_dynamic_access, "matlab_dynamic_field", 1

    Return hir_dynamic_access
End Process

@Reasoning:
Translates MATLAB's three colon-operator forms based on child count:
- 0 children: bare ":" (all-elements sentinel) -> synthetic identifier
  "colon_all" with "matlab_colon_all"=1 metadata;
- 2 children: "start:end" -> HIR range with default step;
- 3 children: "start:step:end" -> HIR range with explicit step.
All forms carry "matlab_colon"=1 metadata so codegen can lower MATLAB's
range semantics (inclusive end, double-typed steps) rather than HIR's
generic range.
@End Reasoning
Process called "translate_colon_expression" takes ctx as Integer, colon_node as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: MATLAB colon operator: start:end or start:step:end or just :
    Let child_count be proc ast_node_child_count from colon_node

    Note: Just ":" (all elements)
    If child_count is equal to 0:
        Let hir_colon be proc hir_create_identifier from HIR with "colon_all"
        proc hir_set_metadata from HIR with hir_colon, "matlab_colon_all", 1
        Return hir_colon
    End If

    Note: start:end (2 arguments)
    If child_count is equal to 2:
        Let start_child be proc ast_node_child with colon_node, 0
        Let hir_start be proc translate_expression with ctx, start_child

        Let end_child be proc ast_node_child with colon_node, 1
        Let hir_end be proc translate_expression with ctx, end_child

        Note: Create HIR range expression (start, end, step=1)
        Let hir_range be proc hir_create_range from HIR with hir_start, hir_end, 0
        proc hir_set_metadata from HIR with hir_range, "matlab_colon", 1
        Return hir_range
    End If

    Note: start:step:end (3 arguments)
    If child_count is equal to 3:
        Set start_child to proc ast_node_child with colon_node, 0
        Set hir_start to proc translate_expression with ctx, start_child

        Let step_child be proc ast_node_child with colon_node, 1
        Let hir_step be proc translate_expression with ctx, step_child

        Set end_child to proc ast_node_child with colon_node, 2
        Set hir_end to proc translate_expression with ctx, end_child

        Note: Create HIR range expression with step
        Set hir_range to proc hir_create_range from HIR with hir_start, hir_end, hir_step
        proc hir_set_metadata from HIR with hir_range, "matlab_colon", 1
        Return hir_range
    End If

    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning:
"@funcName" becomes an HIR_NODE_FUNCTION_POINTER. The target function is
resolved through the symbol table if available; resolved_func can be 0
when the target lives in another file or toolbox — in that case the
function-pointer still records the name so a late binding resolves at
link/load time.
@End Reasoning
Process called "translate_function_handle" takes ctx as Integer, handle_node as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: MATLAB function handle: @functionName
    Let func_name_child be proc ast_node_child with handle_node, 0
    Let func_name be proc ast_node_value from func_name_child

    Note: Lookup function in symbol table
    Let resolved_func be proc lookup_symbol with ctx, func_name

    Note: Create HIR function pointer
    Let base_node be proc hir_create_node from HIR with HIR.HIR_NODE_FUNCTION_POINTER
    Let hir_func_ptr be proc create_hir_function_pointer from HIR with base_node, func_name, resolved_func, HIR.HIR_TYPE_FUNCTION

    Return hir_func_ptr
End Process

@Reasoning:
"@(x,y) body" -> HIR_LAMBDA_EXPR. Pushes a new lexical scope before
translating the body so parameter names mask outer-scope identifiers
inside the lambda. The lambda's free-variable capture (MATLAB closes
over the enclosing workspace at @() evaluation time) is handled by the
HIR semantic phase, not here — this routine just emits the structural
shape.
@End Reasoning
Process called "translate_anonymous_function" takes ctx as Integer, anon_node as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: MATLAB anonymous function: @(x, y) x + y
    proc push_scope from ctx

    Note: Get parameters
    Let params_child be proc ast_node_child with anon_node, 0
    Let hir_params be proc hir_create_parameter_list from HIR

    Let param_count be proc ast_node_child_count from params_child
    Let i be 0

    While i is less than param_count:
        Let param_child be proc ast_node_child with params_child, i
        Let param_name be proc ast_node_value from param_child
        Let hir_param be proc hir_create_parameter from HIR with param_name, HIR.HIR_TYPE_ANY
        proc hir_add_parameter_to_list from HIR with hir_params, hir_param
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    Note: Get body expression
    Let body_child be proc ast_node_child with anon_node, 1
    Let hir_body be proc translate_expression with ctx, body_child

    Note: Create HIR lambda expression
    Let base_node be proc hir_create_node from HIR with HIR.HIR_NODE_LAMBDA_EXPR
    Let hir_lambda be proc create_hir_lambda_expression from HIR with base_node, hir_params, param_count, hir_body, HIR.HIR_TYPE_ANY

    proc pop_scope from ctx
    Return hir_lambda
End Process

@Reasoning:
Lowers MATLAB's "'" and ".'" to a unary HIR_OP_TRANSPOSE. The
"complex_conjugate" parser flag indicates the "'" form, which transposes
AND conjugates complex values; this is captured as
"matlab_complex_conjugate"=1 metadata so codegen can choose the right
runtime primitive ("'" -> conj+transpose; ".'" -> plain transpose).
@End Reasoning
Process called "translate_transpose_expression" takes ctx as Integer, transpose_node as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Get operand
    Let operand_child be proc ast_node_child with transpose_node, 0
    Let hir_operand be proc translate_expression with ctx, operand_child

    Note: Check if complex conjugate transpose (') or regular transpose (.')
    Let is_complex be proc ast_node_has_flag with transpose_node, "complex_conjugate"

    Note: Create HIR unary expression for transpose
    Let base_node be proc hir_create_node from HIR with HIR.HIR_NODE_UNARY_EXPR
    Let hir_transpose be proc create_hir_unary_expression from HIR with base_node, HIR.HIR_OP_TRANSPOSE, hir_operand, HIR.HIR_TYPE_ANY

    If is_complex is equal to 1:
        proc hir_set_metadata from HIR with hir_transpose, "matlab_complex_conjugate", 1
    End If

    Return hir_transpose
End Process
